column5: Okay so it wasnt a big one, but nice lookin eh?  Last chrome of 2008 for me, BRING ON FEBRUARY
Did you get this one one the fly?

Nope I was floating, too cold for the fly.  Notice the orange tinge on the fin and around the mouth? Thats not the camera, this particular river causes a strange orange tinge on the fish in the winter and I have never figured out why. Maybe its because it flows through a bog?
maybe the tinge is from tannic acid?
sweet shaker...Anything is nice at this time of year bud !!!
Nice fish there Kemps, good picture too,  Thans for sharin that

Tell me about it.  I nearly had a heart attack when my float went down!  February, come on buddy get here faster!  Dave I had a PM from steve last week askin if I wanted to get out. I did of course but school got in the way, lets make sure the three of us go bash a river again in the spring

Ya for sure.... Im waiting for the man in the brown suit to deliver my new rod/reel arsenal.... I am sure when they arrive I will be more willing to trek out into some -10 again    PM me with Steve's username... I didn't even know he was on this board
